thread.title: Chicago-to-Las Vegas flight lands safely after reporting possible steering, brakes problem
thread.title_full: Chicago-to-Las Vegas flight lands safely after reporting possible steering, brakes problem - Winnipeg Free Press

author: The Associated Press
title: Chicago-to-Las Vegas flight lands safely after reporting possible steering, brakes problem
text:
LAS VEGAS, Nev. - An airport official says a commercial jetliner from Chicago landed safely in Las Vegas after reporting a possible problem with the aircraft braking and steering system.
McCarran International Airport spokeswoman Christine Crews says United Airlines flight 519 from O'Hare International Airport to Las Vegas declared an in-flight emergency before landing about 2:10 p.m. PDT.
No injuries were reported.
Crews says the Airbus A320 with 157 passengers and crew aboard was towed to a gate as a precaution.
